m_q.target_metric: Percentage of Imposter Scams reports among all reports for military consumers compared to the same percentage for the general population
filters: Demographic = military consumers vs general population
sub_questions: What percentage of military consumer reports are Imposter Scams?
What percentage of general population reports are Imposter Scams?
Is the military percentage higher than the general population percentage?

schema_conflicts: Military data has separate files for different report types (Fraud, Identity Theft, Other) while general data combines them
Military data has additional columns (% Reporting $ Loss, Total $ Loss, Median $ Loss) not in general data

scale_issues: Military data shows top 10 categories only, while general data shows 29 categories
Military data includes only fraud categories, while general data includes all complaint categories
cross_source_conflicts: Military data 'Imposter Scams' count (44,587) appears to be only fraud reports, while general data 'Imposter Scams' count (845,806) includes all reports

format_notes: Military data has percentage values stored as strings with % symbol
Military data has currency values stored as strings with $ and M suffix

constraints: Total general population reports = sum of all # of Reports in 2024_CSN_Report_Categories.csv
derived_filters: Filter to only Imposter Scams category
Calculate percentages relative to total reports for each demographic
